    "summary": "Electronic Engineer graduated from the Universidad Industrial de Santander, UIS, Colombia. Master in Electrical Engineering from the University of Campinas, UNICAMP, Brazil. Ph.D. in Electrical Engineering from the University of Campinas, UNICAMP, Brazil, and the University of Southern Denmark, SDU, Denmark (double-degree program). He spent over a year and a half as a Postdoctoral Researcher at the Electrical Energy Systems group at the Eindhoven University of Technology, TU/e, in The Netherlands. He is an assistant professor at the Intelligent Electrical Power Grids group at the Delft University of Technology and an IEEE Senior Member. At TU Delft, he leads several research activities in Dutch (LIFE, DATALESS, ALING4Energy) and European-funded projects (MAGPIE, DRIVE2X), including the NWO DATALESS Project, where he acts as co-PI. His research topics relate to mathematical programming- and Machine Learning-based control, operation, and planning of sustainable electrical distribution networks.",
